    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut the <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Roll the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice!) and cut in half</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-chorizo-tacos-with-smashed-chilli-peas/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> blanched peas</strong>\u00a0to a pot of\u00a0<strong>boiled water</strong>\u00a0with a pinch of\u00a0<strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 2-3 min or until they're tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and\u00a0return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-chorizo-tacos-with-smashed-chilli-peas/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the peas are cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>natural yoghurt</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) and juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]<strong> </span>lime </strong>in a small bowl \u2013 this is your<strong> tangy garlic\u00a0yoghurt</strong></p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-chorizo-tacos-with-smashed-chilli-peas/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the\u00a0<strong>cooked peas</strong>\u00a0to a low\u00a0heat with a large knob of\u00a0<strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add the\u00a0<strong>chopped</strong> <strong>chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Mash until you're left with a coarse pea mash \u2013 these are your\u00a0<strong>smashed chilli peas</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-chorizo-tacos-with-smashed-chilli-peas/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>\u00a0over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot,\u00a0add the<strong>\u00a0diced chorizo</strong>\u00a0and cook for 4-5 min or until crisped</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-chorizo-tacos-with-smashed-chilli-peas/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the\u00a0<strong>tortillas</strong>\u00a0to a baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 2-3 min or until they're warmed through</p><p>Wash the <strong>rocket</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-chorizo-tacos-with-smashed-chilli-peas/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>haddock bites</strong> to the pan with the chorizo and cook for 3-4 min further, turning once half way, or until the fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-and-chorizo-tacos-with-smashed-chilli-peas/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the <strong>warmed tortillas</strong> with some<strong> tangy\u00a0garlic yoghurt</strong>, <strong>haddock & chorizo</strong>,\u00a0<strong>smashed chilli peas </strong>and\u00a0<strong>rocket</strong></p><p>Garnish with the\u00a0<strong>lime wedges</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
